# Black Theme â€” Always-On Policy

## Mandate
- Black theme is the only supported theme (pure black/dark surfaces). No light toggle. No auto-switch via system preference.
- The application must boot with black styles applied globally.

## Implementation Rules

### 1) HTML Root
- Apply `class="theme-dark"` to the root `<html>` element at all times (SSR and client).

### 2) CSS Variables (shadcn-like)
- Expose black theme tokens from `COLORS.mdc`, `TYPOGRAPHY.mdc`, and `SPACING.mdc` under `:root` and `.theme-dark`.
- Do not define or reference light tokens.

### 3) Component Usage
- All components must reference CSS variables via `hsl(var(--token))` in classes or inline styles as needed.
- Backgrounds must use `var(--background)`, text `var(--foreground)`, borders `var(--border)` via CSS classes.

### 4) Accessibility
- Maintain WCAG 2.1 AA contrast in dark mode.
- Focus outlines must use token-driven color and be visible on dark backgrounds.

### 5) Prohibited
- No light theme assets, toggles, or conditional styles.
- No dynamic theme switching at runtime.

## Verification Checklist
- [ ] Root HTML has `class="theme-dark"` at first paint.
- [ ] CSS variables for tokens are present on `:root`/`.theme-dark`.
- [ ] UI surfaces use background/foreground/border tokens consistently.
- [ ] No references to light tokens or `prefers-color-scheme`.
